&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Assistant Practitioner Norfolk Healthy Child Programme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Norfolk Children &amp; Young People’s Health Service (Cambridgeshire Community Services NHS Trust) is passionate about ensuring every child and young person living in Norfolk has the opportunity to achieve their full potential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, committed individuals who are service user focused to work in the innovative Norfolk Healthy Child Programme. This is a community role which involves working with families both face to face in the community, and also virtually using video consultations and digital resources. You will be self-motivated, able to demonstrate empathy and enjoy working with children &amp; young people to improve health outcomes. It is important that you have strong communication skills and be able to demonstrate experience of partnership working. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Healthy Child Programme delivers services to children &amp; young people 0-19 years. You will be required to demonstrate your skills in specific areas, and to be willing to undertake training relevant to your role across the age range. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All applicants will have excellent verbal, written and computer skills and demonstrate a commitment to personal and professional development as well as supporting the development of others in the team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a fixed term post for 12 months, with the option to work from various locations across Norfolk. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please contact Jo Dennison, Team Leader, for further details: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;joannedennison@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
